5:
Thanks for coming. I know you're
both busy, but you still went out of
your way to help me.
9:
Please, you're the one that's always
helping us!
13:
Shibuya's restoration is proceeding
well, but it's still severely lacking in
medical facilities.
16:
We owe you a debt of gratitude for
providing us with so much medicine.
Thank you, Hartlief.
20:
It's nothing. I'm just doing what I can
to help.
26:
Welcome back! Are you on your own
today?
29:
That I am. The Guild Knights are
shorthanded, but what else is new?
31:
Speakin' of which, do you have any
medicine that will help me get
through these 24-hour shifts?
33:
Seein' these youngins makes me
wanna do more to maintain the
peace, y'know? And I've got a boy of
my own to protect too!
35:
Anything you have to help me
perform my duties would be
appreciated! I'm sure it would put
the mayor at ease too!
38:
I'm sorry, but I can't prescribe
anything like that.
41: I understand how you feel, I really do.
45:
But you already work too hard.
You've got bags under your eyes.
You know you need more rest, don't
you?
48: What? But I can't slack off...
51:
It's not medicine you need but good
old-fashioned sleep.
54:
As an herbalist, it's my job to
prescribe medicine that suit my
patients' needs. I won't give you
anything that could worsen your
condition.
58:
Think of getting proper rest as one
of your duties. Here, start by
warming yourself up with some
soup.
62: Yeah, I s'pose you're right... As usual!
65:
S-sir, come quick! Your boy's fallen ill
with a fever!
68: You go. We'll look after things here.
72:
Thank you! I'll come back as soon as
I can!
75:
Hey! Wake up! He's burning up...
What do I do, what do I do?!
78:
Ma'am, can you tell me his
symptoms?
81:
H-he was playing outside all
morning, and he was fine. But
suddenly he came down with a high
fever and collapsed.
87:
A neck rash... It must be the cold
that's going around.
91:
I-is he okay?! Will he be all right? If
he rests, will he—
95:
Don't worry. He'll be fine with rest
and medicine.
98:
I'll prepare a treatment right away.
Can you boil some water, please?
101:
Fetch some clean towels too. We'll
need to periodically wipe his sweat
to prevent him from feeling chilly.
105:
Here's a recipe for an herbal soup
that strengthens the immune
system. I suggest you both have
some as well.
108: Am... Am I going... to live?
111: Don't worry. I'll get you better.
114:
I'll need your help to care for your
son.
117:
The important thing is to remain
calm and do all you can!
126: Wow, I already feel so much better!
129: I'm glad the medicine did its job.
132:
But you're still healing, so make sure
you get enough rest.
135:
Oh, and make sure you wash your
hands frequently. Now, be a good
boy and stay inside today. Pinky
promise?
141:
The two of you should take it easy at
home today as well. We don't want
to risk infecting anyone else.
144:
Right you are. I guess the occasional
day off never hurt anyone. We owe
you!
146:
All right, my boy! Looks like you're
spendin' the day at home playin'
with your old man!
150:
Thank you so much, Hartlief. I feel
awful that you spent all night
looking after our son.
153:
Not at all. There's nothing I enjoy
more than seeing my patients smile.
Take care!
156:
Thank you, Santa Lady! Happy
holidays!
